Core features:

 * Password reminder

 * Force HTTPS also for registration form (see note at PytisModule.action_add()).

 * Allow attachment and extension module management to page owner

 * Remove the dbname column -- get the database name from somewhere else

 * Delete stray files after deletion triggered in the database (cascade)

 * Serve favicon and robots.txt

 * RSS links in page header and panels

 * Image allignment and link title in the LCG formatting manual

 * Default language when Accept-Language is not set at all

 * Locking

 * Change log and Last-Modified HTTP header support

 * Reencoding HTML attachments?

 * Cache exported HTML for structured text content in DB?

 * Print preview

 * Support multithreaded Apache MPM (currently broken)


Extensions:

 * Image galeries

 * Blog

 * Articles

